		"description": "<p>You may use an action to breath out a 15 foot cone or 5 foot wide 30 long foot line.<span style=\"mso-spacerun: yes;\">&nbsp; </span>You choose the shape of this breath when you gain this ability and cannot change it. Creatures in the area must make a Dexterity saving throw against your warlock spell save DC or take 2d6 damage of your draconic damage type on a failure or half damage on a success. If your draconic damage type is cold or poison, they must instead make a Constitution saving throw.<span style=\"mso-spacerun: yes;\">&nbsp;</span>This damage increases by 1d6 at 10th level, and again at 15th and 20th level.<span style=\"mso-spacerun: yes;\"> </span>At 14th level the area increases to a 30 foot cone or a 5 foot wide, 60 foot long line.<span style=\"mso-spacerun: yes;\"> </span>You can use this attack a number of times equal to your proficiency bonus and regain all expended uses when you finish a short or long rest.</p>",
